				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A game that scrolls only horizontally might use a circular buffer 32 metatiles wide by 12 to 15 metatiles high to cache the map for collision and partial updates. At one byte per 16x16-pixel metatile, this should take just shy of one-fourth of the CPU RAM.</div>

